message.content: Sara needs a total of 8 test tubes for her three experiments, and the first experiment requires 2 test tubes. This means that there are 8 - 2 = 6 test tubes left over for the remaining two experiments. Since each experiment requires the same number of test tubes, each experiment will need 6 / 2 = 3 test tubes. Therefore, Sara needs 3 test tubes for each of the remaining two experiments.
